she'll hang upside down. I want a playful expression.

268
00:19:02.899 --> 00:19:05.440
Why don't you look at me when you talk? It bothers me.

269
00:19:05.670 --> 00:19:08.470
Well, I feel awkward looking at you.

270
00:19:11.950 --> 00:19:13.980
Are you trying to act pretty?

271
00:19:18.420 --> 00:19:20.020
Why would I do that?

272
00:19:22.819 --> 00:19:24.289
Putting my hair behind my ear?

273
00:19:24.889 --> 00:19:26.559
You did that.

274
00:19:27.059 --> 00:19:28.260
What...

275
00:19:28.629 --> 00:19:29.760
How is this acting pretty?

276
00:19:29.760 --> 00:19:32.069
I just put my hair back because it was in my face.

277
00:19:32.069 --> 00:19:34.869
Look. How is this acting pretty? I was putting my hair back.

278
00:19:35.670 --> 00:19:38.399
Why are you putting the moves on me...

279
00:19:38.910 --> 00:19:40.010
so blatantly?

280
00:19:40.010 --> 00:19:41.369
Don't do this.

281
00:19:42.240 --> 00:19:44.809
What... Don't do what?

282
00:19:46.809 --> 00:19:48.079
Was he traumatized?

283
00:19:49.450 --> 00:19:50.819
I can't even touch my hair.

284
00:20:13.109 --> 00:20:14.470
He must've felt unpleasant when I made the moves.

285
00:20:14.470 --> 00:20:15.710
No wonder it didn't work.

286
00:20:18.950 --> 00:20:20.549
It must have been very traumatizing.

287
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:39.730
He won't even let me look.

288
00:20:50.280 --> 00:20:51.809
That was so spicy.

289
00:20:52.910 --> 00:20:54.879
My tongue's burning.

290
00:21:01.990 --> 00:21:03.859
She likes spicy foods.

291
00:21:04.260 --> 00:21:05.289
Why is she...

292
00:21:06.059 --> 00:21:08.629
When you talk, you need to whisper.

293
00:21:09.329 --> 00:21:10.829
If you whisper,

294
00:21:10.829 --> 00:21:13.670
the other person will naturally lean over to listen.

295
00:21:14.170 --> 00:21:17.299
Then your face will become closer to theirs.

296
00:21:17.639 --> 00:21:21.470
And that will make that person's heart flutter.

297
00:21:23.339 --> 00:21:25.410
Gosh, why did I eat that?

298
00:21:27.349 --> 00:21:31.349
Why are you whispering? Talk louder so I can hear you.

299
00:21:33.289 --> 00:21:34.389
The chili pepper was too spicy.

300
00:21:38.789 --> 00:21:41.559
Hey, why are you breathing like that?

301
00:21:45.500 --> 00:21:48.000
Why... Why are you sucking on the candy?

302
00:21:48.670 --> 00:21:49.970
Must you suck it like that?

303
00:21:50.569 --> 00:21:53.069
Do you want one as well? I should've offered you one.

304
00:21:53.069 --> 00:21:54.309
I'm sorry.

305
00:21:55.069 --> 00:21:56.309
Here you go.

306
00:21:56.410 --> 00:21:58.410
- Here's a candy. - No, it's okay. Stop.

307
00:21:58.510 --> 00:22:02.319
Ms. Jang, if you keep doing that, things will get dangerous.

308
00:22:04.020 --> 00:22:05.079
What...

309
00:22:08.149 --> 00:22:10.119
Why would this put me in danger?

310
00:22:19.299 --> 00:22:20.899
(Urologist, Moon Soo)

311
00:22:27.710 --> 00:22:28.839
Dr. Moon.

312
00:22:29.410 --> 00:22:32.980
I'm too healthy.

313
00:22:34.849 --> 00:22:37.950
I personally think you're too ethical.

314
00:22:38.180 --> 00:22:40.089
You know it won't do you any good if you keep holding it in.

315
00:22:40.319 --> 00:22:41.819
Don't hold it in too much.

316
00:22:41.920 --> 00:22:43.289
But I told you.

317
00:22:43.760 --> 00:22:47.190
This woman wants kids.

318
00:22:48.859 --> 00:22:51.730
I was marked with an "X",

319
00:22:51.960 --> 00:22:54.670
- but I think I'm still a candidate. - What?

320
00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:57.200
A triangle. I won't even ask for a star.

321
00:22:57.670 --> 00:22:58.940
A triangle.

322
00:22:59.869 --> 00:23:03.109
A triangle. That's all I ask for.

323
00:23:04.139 --> 00:23:05.210
Is that not possible?

324
00:23:05.680 --> 00:23:08.109
(Dachae Media)

325
00:23:17.889 --> 00:23:21.230
Gosh, I need to learn how to b-boy and do the Bongsan mask dance.

326
00:23:23.329 --> 00:23:24.859
(A saxophone serenade and video)

327
00:23:27.869 --> 00:23:29.970
What is he so serious about?

328
00:23:30.170 --> 00:23:31.170
Hyo Joo.

329
00:23:32.670 --> 00:23:33.740
What are you doing?

330
00:23:34.809 --> 00:23:35.879
It's nothing.

331
00:23:44.420 --> 00:23:46.549
- Is that from the studio? - Yes.

332
00:23:47.720 --> 00:23:49.990
Is it from Mr. Han?

333
00:23:50.289 --> 00:23:52.020
No, he was on his way out.

334
00:23:52.660 --> 00:23:53.760
Oh, I see.

335
00:24:03.339 --> 00:24:05.270
- What's that? - Red ginseng.

336
00:24:05.670 --> 00:24:06.710
I need some energy.

337
00:24:08.569 --> 00:24:11.910
Ha Ri, you always give me tips,

338
00:24:11.910 --> 00:24:14.510
so let me return the favor.

339
00:24:15.010 --> 00:24:16.849
- In order to seduce a guy... - Hey.

340
00:24:18.950 --> 00:24:20.420
Thank you.

341
00:24:23.359 --> 00:24:26.329
What's this? Did she give me this to shut me up?

342
00:24:26.589 --> 00:24:29.260
She quickly figured out that it wasn't worth listening.

343
00:24:42.309 --> 00:24:45.379
What? What are you doing here? You don't have a shoot today.

344
00:24:45.579 --> 00:24:47.510
I came to check the backdrop papers.

345
00:24:47.510 --> 00:24:48.750
If it's not here, I need to prepare it.

346
00:24:49.149 --> 00:24:51.680
- Are you going somewhere? - Oh, the hospital.

347
00:24:51.879 --> 00:24:55.589
Is no one else in the studio?

348
00:24:56.889 --> 00:24:59.260
I don't know where Mr. Han went.

349
00:24:59.559 --> 00:25:01.460
Lock the door if no one's here.

350
00:25:01.629 --> 00:25:03.399
Okay, see you.

351
00:25:08.869 --> 00:25:12.410
I'll quickly check and leave.

352
00:25:13.539 --> 00:25:16.010
Let's see if it's here.

353
00:25:18.379 --> 00:25:19.450
No, not this.

354
00:25:21.609 --> 00:25:23.980
Let me check.

355
00:25:24.579 --> 00:25:25.690
What?

356
00:25:26.549 --> 00:25:27.750
Why won't it move?

357
00:25:39.569 --> 00:25:40.730
Oh, my gosh!

358
00:25:42.339 --> 00:25:44.539
Gosh, I'm sorry. I mean, thank you.

359
00:25:45.910 --> 00:25:46.970
I'm sorry.

360
00:25:50.480 --> 00:25:51.480
Are you okay?

361
00:25:52.410 --> 00:25:53.579
Yes, I'm okay.

362
00:25:54.250 --> 00:25:55.609
- Hey, wait. - Yes?

363
00:26:03.119 --> 00:26:04.220
I remember now.

364
00:26:07.930 --> 00:26:08.960
Remember what?

365
00:26:10.799 --> 00:26:13.099
That day, when we first met...

366
00:26:19.665 --> 00:26:21.925
That day, when we first met...

367
00:26:26.135 --> 00:26:27.905
I remembered what I did that day.

368
00:26:29.034 --> 00:26:31.774
I finally get why you said you felt unpleasant.

369
00:26:38.375 --> 00:26:39.385
Right.

370
00:26:42.445 --> 00:26:43.514
That's it?

371
00:26:44.215 --> 00:26:46.784
What more do I need to say?

372
00:26:48.284 --> 00:26:49.925
It's all in the past.

373
00:26:51.425 --> 00:26:53.125
But you told me it felt unpleasant.

374
00:26:53.925 --> 00:26:57.764
I mean, you could even sue me for that.

375
00:27:01.905 --> 00:27:04.334
It wasn't that unpleasant for me...

376
00:27:04.705 --> 00:27:06.205
to sue you.

377
00:27:10.274 --> 00:27:14.185
Back then, I was very sensitive.

378
00:27:16.254 --> 00:27:17.254
Yes.

379
00:27:18.215 --> 00:27:20.784
But it did...

380
00:27:22.084 --> 00:27:24.594
console me.

381
00:27:28.994 --> 00:27:32.865
Then why are you being so complicated?

382
00:27:36.774 --> 00:27:39.975
Back then, it was just a light feeling.

383
00:27:39.975 --> 00:27:43.145
But that's not the case for both of us...

384
00:27:43.544 --> 00:27:44.645
this time.

385
00:27:46.685 --> 00:27:47.915
Although, it didn't last long.

386
00:27:58.524 --> 00:27:59.594
Ms. Jang.

387
00:28:02.524 --> 00:28:03.564
Did you really...

388
00:28:06.034 --> 00:28:08.665
think of me as a man?

389
00:28:14.105 --> 00:28:15.105
What?

390
00:28:36.165 --> 00:28:38.094
Well, he's obviously a man.

391
00:28:44.675 --> 00:28:47.445
Hey, it's time to go to work.

392
00:28:50.044 --> 00:28:52.244
Gosh, what's his problem?

393
00:29:00.455 --> 00:29:02.625
Do Ah, you like beef soup, don't you?

394
00:29:02.794 --> 00:29:05.725
You'll get that for lunch today, so I hope you enjoy it.

395
00:29:06.665 --> 00:29:07.764
There she is.

396
00:29:09.665 --> 00:29:12.234
Hey, what kind of a normal guy in Korea...

397
00:29:12.234 --> 00:29:14.234
would willingly donate their sperm to you?

398
00:29:14.465 --> 00:29:15.734
Whoever offers it to you has got to be weird.

399
00:29:16.175 --> 00:29:17.675
This is what Einstein said.

400
00:29:18.074 --> 00:29:21.205
"Common sense is the collection of prejudices acquired by age 18."

401
00:29:21.504 --> 00:29:23.774
Don't speak as if what you think is common sense.

402
00:29:24.215 --> 00:29:26.185
Some would've donated it for a good cause,

403
00:29:26.185 --> 00:29:27.445
so don't speak ill of them.

404
00:29:27.744 --> 00:29:29.244
I get what kind of situation you are in...

405
00:29:29.244 --> 00:29:30.655
and how you must feel right now.

406
00:29:31.155 --> 00:29:33.754
But do you really think this is realistically possible?

407
00:29:34.084 --> 00:29:35.125
And of all people...

408
00:29:36.425 --> 00:29:37.695
Why are you nagging at me...

409
00:29:37.695 --> 00:29:39.155
even when I've offered to take Do Ah to the daycare center?

410
00:29:39.155 --> 00:29:41.024
- What's your standard? - Standard for what?

411
00:29:41.425 --> 00:29:43.465
What's your standard when choosing the right sperm?

412
00:29:45.094 --> 00:29:47.504
It needs to be powerful enough to get me pregnant in one go.

413
00:29:48.465 --> 00:29:50.574
How will you ever know that?

414
00:29:50.574 --> 00:29:52.435
Do you have see-through vision? How are you going to tell?

415
00:29:52.435 --> 00:29:55.475
I'm looking for a young, healthy guy who doesn't drink or smoke.

416
00:29:55.705 --> 00:29:57.115
Is that Eu Ddeum?

417
00:29:58.314 --> 00:30:00.744
- What? - Have you made up your mind?

418
00:30:02.814 --> 00:30:04.955
By any chance, am I...

419
00:30:06.455 --> 00:30:07.484
one of the candidates?

420
00:30:08.855 --> 00:30:10.094
Would you donate yours to me?

421
00:30:12.294 --> 00:30:13.324
What?

422
00:30:17.764 --> 00:30:19.165
I'm quite conservative, you know.

423
00:30:21.865 --> 00:30:23.304
Why would I give you mine...

424
00:30:24.675 --> 00:30:26.205
when I could just marry you?

425
00:30:27.175 --> 00:30:29.004
You're super annoying, you know that?

426
00:30:29.044 --> 00:30:30.774
Let's just go, sister.

427
00:30:31.215 --> 00:30:33.014
- You're the worst. - Seriously?

428
00:30:33.014 --> 00:30:36.145
Why does she keep calling me that? Does she think I'm her sister?

429
00:30:37.054 --> 00:30:38.155
Just you wait and see.

430
00:30:38.685 --> 00:30:41.084
"Honey, sweetheart."

431
00:30:41.185 --> 00:30:42.855
"My love."

432
00:30:43.554 --> 00:30:44.725
That's what you'll soon call me.

433
00:30:45.054 --> 00:30:46.695
"Artificial insemination"?

434
00:30:47.264 --> 00:30:49.834
It's not impossible per se, but the odds can't be guaranteed.

435
00:30:50.534 --> 00:30:53.135
Why would she think of that instead of getting married?

436
00:30:54.965 --> 00:30:57.635
It must be easier for her to find sperm instead of a husband.

437
00:30:57.905 --> 00:31:00.004
- As if it's that easier. - Tell me about it.

438
00:31:00.475 --> 00:31:03.774
She thinks sperm donation is the same as donating blood.

439
00:31:05.044 --> 00:31:07.844
Is she queer...

440
00:31:08.014 --> 00:31:09.584
or is she just sick of men?

441
00:31:11.784 --> 00:31:13.584
- Well... - I think I can tell.

442
00:31:14.225 --> 00:31:15.355
Is she well-off?

443
00:31:15.725 --> 00:31:18.455
- Well... - Then her chances are slim.

444
00:31:20.695 --> 00:31:23.294
She could easily provide for a man on her own.

445
00:31:23.294 --> 00:31:26.564
Also, she's incredibly beautiful and lovely.

446
00:31:27.734 --> 00:31:28.865
Then what's her issue?

447
00:31:30.504 --> 00:31:32.074
She doesn't have any.

448
00:31:33.105 --> 00:31:35.244
For her, finding a sperm donor might be better...

449
00:31:35.774 --> 00:31:37.145
than marrying some random guy.

450
00:31:37.875 --> 00:31:39.074
Then what's the problem?

451
00:31:39.645 --> 00:31:42.814
I'm torn to think of her marrying someone else.

452
00:31:43.385 --> 00:31:45.484
But having another man's child?

453
00:31:45.855 --> 00:31:48.955
It seems like something that can't be undone.

454
00:31:50.254 --> 00:31:53.465
Why would you want to undo it? Do you want to date her yourself?

455
00:31:54.225 --> 00:31:56.334
Then date her right now.

456
00:31:56.794 --> 00:32:00.465
Is she too pretty to date or marry a single father who's divorced?

457
00:32:00.534 --> 00:32:03.405
What's wrong with being divorced when I also have a sweet daughter?

458
00:32:04.334 --> 00:32:05.635
She might think otherwise.

459
00:32:06.574 --> 00:32:07.645
Right, well...

460
00:32:08.375 --> 00:32:09.445
I'll see you around.

461
00:32:09.814 --> 00:32:10.844
Sure.

462
00:32:20.125 --> 00:32:21.254
Have you eaten?

463
00:32:21.824 --> 00:32:24.395
I haven't. Care to join me?

464
00:32:24.494 --> 00:32:26.764
Don't talk to me like nothing happened.

465
00:32:27.195 --> 00:32:28.925
It makes me hate you even more.

466
00:32:30.594 --> 00:32:33.834
Can we at least get together for Do Ah's first birthday photo?

467
00:32:33.834 --> 00:32:35.304
She only gets to take it once.

468
00:32:35.865 --> 00:32:38.274
- I should be in it. - Don't think about using her.

469
00:32:38.675 --> 00:32:39.705
I won't ever agree to it.

470
00:32:42.375 --> 00:32:44.114
Are you thinking about marrying Ha Ri?

471
00:32:46.545 --> 00:32:47.614
It's been on my mind.

472
00:32:50.585 --> 00:32:51.855
Ha Ri...

473
00:32:52.554 --> 00:32:55.424
will be furious when she finds out that you're only using her...

474
00:32:55.924 --> 00:32:57.125
to get back at me.

475
00:33:02.025 --> 00:33:04.134
Promise to meet up for a meal sometime.

476
00:33:11.835 --> 00:33:12.975
Yes, Ms. Choi.

477
00:33:13.074 --> 00:33:16.074
Eu Ddeum, I asked you to send the products.

478
00:33:16.074 --> 00:33:17.315
They're not here!

479
00:33:20.284 --> 00:33:22.214
The model is on her way, so what now?

480
00:33:25.985 --> 00:33:29.625
Yes, of course. I'll call you back.

481
00:33:31.225 --> 00:33:32.525
What did they say?

482
00:33:33.494 --> 00:33:35.994
That I didn't mention it. I thought I had though.

483
00:33:36.835 --> 00:33:38.264
Are you kidding me?

484
00:33:38.264 --> 00:33:40.835
The baby model is already on her way from Gyeongju!

485
00:33:40.835 --> 00:33:42.835
I also have a photoshoot in Chuncheon...

486
00:33:42.835 --> 00:33:44.605
so I need to hurry and go after this.

487
00:33:44.674 --> 00:33:47.775
They agreed to call a nearby store,

488
00:33:48.145 --> 00:33:50.775
so I'll bring over the products. Excuse me.

489
00:33:51.844 --> 00:33:54.014
You don't even have a car. I'm coming with you!

490
00:33:55.985 --> 00:33:58.214
Hurry up. Move!

491
00:33:59.784 --> 00:34:01.384
Yes, this is The Baby.

492
00:34:01.455 --> 00:34:03.094
Didn't the head office call?

493
00:34:03.755 --> 00:34:05.594
Yes, products that were on display sounds fine.

494
00:34:06.525 --> 00:34:08.565
Yes, I'll be right there.

495
00:34:12.094 --> 00:34:14.205
- Get in. - Sure.

496
00:34:20.744 --> 00:34:22.145
Hurry!

497
00:34:27.284 --> 00:34:29.045
- Sorry about this. - Your belt.

498
00:34:35.924 --> 00:34:37.625
If I have to book another model,

499
00:34:37.625 --> 00:34:40.025
I'm going to call you every night just to torture you.

500
00:34:40.395 --> 00:34:43.565
If I get an earful for rescheduling this photoshoot,

501
00:34:44.435 --> 00:34:47.065
I'll nag you every morning until your ears bleed.

502
00:34:48.165 --> 00:34:50.634
And, if Ha Ri scolds me for this,

503
00:34:50.634 --> 00:34:52.804
I'll make you go shopping with me every weekend.

504
00:34:53.804 --> 00:34:55.205
That I can do!

505
00:34:55.475 --> 00:34:57.214
- What? - You can call me anytime.

506
00:34:57.214 --> 00:34:58.545
I'll be your porter.

507
00:35:00.714 --> 00:35:02.844
I won't make you just come shopping with me.

508
00:35:04.815 --> 00:35:05.985
You'll also have to buy me lunch.

509
00:35:06.315 --> 00:35:08.784
Yes, I'll buy. Even dessert.

510
00:35:09.485 --> 00:35:11.094
It won't end there.

511
00:35:11.795 --> 00:35:13.324
You'll have to treat me to a movie, too.

512
00:35:13.324 --> 00:35:16.324
Sure thing. Tell me when there's a movie you want to see.

513
00:35:16.324 --> 00:35:17.395
I'll get the tickets.

514
00:35:20.304 --> 00:35:21.634
Good job!

515
00:35:22.235 --> 00:35:23.804
Once more.

516
00:35:24.435 --> 00:35:25.904
How pretty.

517
00:35:27.944 --> 00:35:29.705
Great, smile!

518
00:35:30.275 --> 00:35:32.775
(Jambi Studio)

519
00:35:44.594 --> 00:35:45.594
I'm sorry.

520
00:35:46.824 --> 00:35:48.864
I'll only let it slide this once.

521
00:35:49.125 --> 00:35:51.594
You're still a newbie, so mistakes can be made.

522
00:35:52.235 --> 00:35:55.335
But your personal life shouldn't distract you like this.

523
00:35:56.205 --> 00:35:58.674
- Sorry? - Tell me what's on your mind.

524
00:36:00.975 --> 00:36:01.975
Well...

525
00:36:04.275 --> 00:36:05.275
It's nothing.

526
00:36:08.985 --> 00:36:11.255
I don't think it's right for me to tell you.

527
00:36:12.654 --> 00:36:14.085
It'll ruin my plan.

528
00:36:14.755 --> 00:36:17.924
How do you want to say it then?

529
00:36:18.094 --> 00:36:20.194
Instead of worrying about it alone,

530
00:36:20.194 --> 00:36:21.725
discuss your options with me.

531
00:36:22.065 --> 00:36:23.464
I'll pretend not to know anything.

532
00:36:28.364 --> 00:36:30.674
Well, you see...

533
00:36:35.505 --> 00:36:37.214
I'm trying...

